Package arcade.agent.module

Class MetabolismComplex

java.lang.Object
arcade.agent.module.Metabolism
arcade.agent.module.MetabolismComplex
All Implemented Interfaces:
Module, java.io.Serializable
public class MetabolismComplex
extends Metabolism
Extension of Metabolism for complex metabolism.

MetabolismComplex explicitly includes pyruvate intermediate between glycolysis and oxidative phosphorylation and glucose uptake is based on cell surface area. Metabolic preference between glycolysis and oxidative phosphorylation is controlled by the META_PREF parameter. The glycolysis pathway will compensate if there is not enough oxygen to meet energetic requirements through the oxidative phosphorylation pathway given the specified metabolic preference.

MetabolismComplex will increase cell mass (using specified fractions of internal glucose and pyruvate) if:

  • cell is dividing and less than double in size
  • cell is below critical mass for maintenance
MetabolismComplex will decrease cell mass if:
  • cell has negative energy levels indicating insufficient nutrients
  • cell is above critical mass for maintenance

Internal pyruvate is removed through conversion to lactate.

    • MetabolismComplex

      public MetabolismComplex​(Cell c, Simulation sim)
      Creates a complex Metabolism module.

      Module has internal glucose and pyruvate. Metabolic preference (META_PREF) parameter is drawn from a Parameter distribution and the distribution is updated with the new mean.

      Parameters:
      c - the TissueCell the module is associated with
      sim - the simulation instance
